    {
        "content": "<p>And another</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\"># from this</span>\n<span class=\"n\">stmt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Sqlite</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">prepare!</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"ss\">path</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">db_path</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"ss\">query</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"SELECT id, task FROM todos WHERE status = :status;\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map_err</span><span class=\"p\">(\\</span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">ServerErr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"Failed to prepare Sqlite statement: $(Inspect.to_str(err))\"</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># to this</span>\n<span class=\"n\">stmt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Sqlite</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">prepare!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"ss\">path</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">db_path</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"ss\">query</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"SELECT id, task FROM todos WHERE status = :status;\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map_err</span><span class=\"p\">(\\</span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">ServerErr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"Failed to prepare Sqlite statement: $(Inspect.to_str(err))\"</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492603101,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736380336
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't mean to be nitpicky... just documenting these as I see them</p>",
        "id": 492603127,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736380352
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I presume we should be able to fix this by saying anything in a PNC apply node that only has one arg, and that arg is a closure or a record, we allow it to stay on the same lines as the PNC braces</p>",
        "id": 492603366,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736380466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we need any other examples unless they can't be fixed by this rule</p>",
        "id": 492603394,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736380485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is the standard style for all collections</p>",
        "id": 492608137,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383168
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And PNC args are in a collection</p>",
        "id": 492608148,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383176
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the standard style is Bad</p>",
        "id": 492608157,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736383188
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And we should change it</p>",
        "id": 492608162,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736383193
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is for args</p>",
        "id": 492608172,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383201
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(when it's for a single item)</p>",
        "id": 492608218,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736383206
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I’m not disagreeing</p>",
        "id": 492608223,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383210
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just context setting</p>",
        "id": 492608232,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It’ll be a small change</p>",
        "id": 492608250,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383231
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I might be able to do it tonight</p>",
        "id": 492608260,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736383239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But in the morning for sure</p>",
        "id": 492608272,
