        "timestamp": 1736383248
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Definitely not urgent</p>",
        "id": 492608309,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736383275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep, not urgent!</p>",
        "id": 492608335,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736383308
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel so much pressure</p>",
        "id": 492610327,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736384630
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>\"More weight.\"</p>",
        "id": 492610373,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736384644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To be clear</p>",
        "id": 492610407,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736384676
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We are saying that the style for PNC that the trailing paren is always tucked up tight?</p>",
        "id": 492610448,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736384711
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or only with a single multiline arg?</p>",
        "id": 492610463,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736384723
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>with a single multiline arg IMO</p>",
        "id": 492610584,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736384816
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, actually</p>",
        "id": 492610606,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736384827
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My definition would be that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>if there is only one argument, even if it's multiline, the opening parens should touch the start of the first argument</li>\n<li>if any of the args are multiline, the closing parens should come on a new line with indentation at the start of the function name up on the first line<ul>\n<li>unless it's a record and there's only one arg, then put that last parens at the end of the record (and maybe a tuple?)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 492610924,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736385056
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think your second rule is “any collection that is the sole argument should have no new lines between its braces and the parens of the apply</p>",
        "id": 492619982,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736391002
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But other multiline expressions should (another apply, when, if, etc)</p>",
        "id": 492620083,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736391066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When I’m done fixing my moms computer and I can use mine again I’ll type out examples</p>",
        "id": 492620136,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736391114
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>beeeeeeen there</p>",
        "id": 492620193,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736391131
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/pnc.20formatting.20records/near/492620193\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>beeeeeeen there</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Never buy a new SSD for your moms computer for Christmas</p>",
        "id": 492620282,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736391211
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or pay GeekSquad to install it</p>",
        "id": 492620407,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736391292
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Those rules make sense</p>",
        "id": 492625443,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736394467
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's the concept floating around of things being \"outdentable\", and I think we should try to follow that</p>",
        "id": 492636381,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736400834
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's what already drives formatting of things like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>foo = {\n  1,\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>rather than:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>foo =\n    {\n        1,\n    }\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492636511,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736400890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That also applies to closures</p>",
        "id": 492636551,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736400907
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(and, IIRC, <code>when</code>, etc etc)</p>",
        "id": 492636611,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736400942
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But for example, it doesn't apply to <code>if</code>, since that looks weird with the outdented \"else\"</p>",
        "id": 492636687,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736400966
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the rule I'd suggest here is:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If the collection has exactly one member,</li>\n<li>and, that member is multi-line</li>\n<li>and, that member is \"outdentable\"</li>\n</ul>\n<p>then we do the formatting suggested here</p>",
        "id": 492636921,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736401091
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm considering outdentable is somewhat flexible here</p>",
        "id": 492636950,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736401112
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In particular, I think this is reasonable to do with single-element lists as well</p>",
        "id": 492636990,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736401140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That makes sense! I don't know how that applies to lambdas, though. I feel like having the closing parens on a new line:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">item_list</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">item</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">first</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">second</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">item</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">first</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">second</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is better than putting the parens on the \"outdentable\" function body:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">item_list</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">item</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">first</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">second</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">item</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">first</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">second</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492677486,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736416106
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Seems so special-casey</p>",
        "id": 492697758,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736422102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One way to think about this would be the additional requirement that the last line of the inner thing must be “short”. A closing brace is short. A line from a lambda or a when expr is not in general short, so we’d define it as such.</p>",
        "id": 492715393,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1736427387
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think when using PNC apply (in Patterns or Exprs) you would like the following:</p>\n<h2>When there is a single arg and it is a single-line collection with no space after stay inline with the apply</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Something\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Here\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Stays the same</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h2>When there is a single arg and it is a multi-line collection the start of the collection touches the open paren, and then end touches the closing paren:</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Something\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Here\"</span>\n<span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Something\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Here\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h2>When there are multiple args, all but the last arg are single-line and the last arg is a multi-line collection the start of the collection stays on the same line as the open paren, and then end touches the closing paren:</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Something\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Here\"</span>\n<span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Something\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Here\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h2>When there is a single arg and that arg is a multi-line lambda the lambda header touches the open parens, the function body is indented, and the closing parens goes to a newline</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(\\</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(\\</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h2>When there are multiple args, all but the last arg are single-line and the last arg is a multi-line lambda the lambda header stays on the same the open parens, the function body is indented, and the closing parens goes to a newline</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">\\</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">\\</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I think the question is what is the handling of <code>when</code> and <code>if</code>?  Do we prefer this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"something else\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"something else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"this\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"something else\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Original</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">some_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"this\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"something else\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Formatted</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Or would you rather have the <code>when</code> on the same line here?  I'm assuming the <code>if..then</code> has to be forced on to a new line and outdent the whole thing.</p>",
        "id": 492743273,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736434794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Forcing when and if on a new line is good!</p>",
        "id": 492784746,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736445758
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Trying to decide if when and if should make the whole thing multiline and outdented</p>",
        "id": 492801923,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736451059
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's my inclination</p>",
        "id": 492803312,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736451500
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Based on what Josh said above, I think <code>if</code> and <code>when</code> aren't \"short\"</p>",
        "id": 492803736,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736451649
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And in addition, they have a target expression they match over that gives context</p>",
        "id": 492803990,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736451733
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And it's nice to have that closer to their bodies</p>",
        "id": 492804032,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736451750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rather than on the same line as the called function, 4 tab widths to the right</p>",
        "id": 492804108,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736451773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, we just have to make sure we define “short”. Like is a nested apply “short”?</p>",
        "id": 492828889,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736460730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep, what is \"short\"</p>",
        "id": 492828971,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736460765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By nested apply do you mean <code>func.call(second_func.call(a, b, c))</code>?</p>",
        "id": 492829014,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736460784
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep</p>",
        "id": 492859077,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736474775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think \"short\" means \"this thing has indentation at its end at the same level as its start\"</p>",
        "id": 492859387,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736474915
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>E.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">func</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">call</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">})</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492859428,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736474937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since the <code>}</code> is where <code>func</code> starts its indentation, even though it \"outdented\" in the record fields</p>",
        "id": 492859508,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736474975
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So that would include PNC applies</p>",
        "id": 492859517,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736474981
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So all collections and PNC applies(which are an expr and an arg collection)</p>",
        "id": 492859601,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Where \"outdented\" means \"the middle of this this has indentation\"</p>",
        "id": 492859604,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736475010
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess as long as the func itself is singleline</p>",
        "id": 492859626,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475020
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, that's easy enough logic to implement</p>",
        "id": 492859674,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep, if you do </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">func</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">call</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">arg1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">arg2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">123</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492859705,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736475062
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll get this banged out and then time for new lambda syntax</p>",
        "id": 492859714,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd expect that to format to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">func</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">call</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">arg1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">arg2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">123</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492859759,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736475085
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, I meant something weird like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>func.call(arg1, arg2, (if blah then\n  func_one\nelse\n  func_two)(some_other_arg))\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492859875,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475126
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which would format to this I assume:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">func</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">call</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">arg1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">arg2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">blah</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">func_one</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">func_two</span><span class=\"p\">)(</span><span class=\"n\">some_other_arg</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 492859957,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736475177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh lol, yeah</p>",
